<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2828] HTable unnecessarily coupled with HMaster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2828</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HTable constructor calls &quot;getCurrentNrHRS()&quot; to get the region server count for thread pool creation.  This code calls HBaseAdmin.getClusterStatus() &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;aka: the HMaster&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; to get the server count.  This information can be scraped from counting the ZooKeeper /hbase/rs/--- ZNodes.  Need to remove unnecessary master queries when ZooKeeper can do the same job.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12468963">HBASE-2828</key>
            <summary>HTable unnecessarily coupled with HMaster</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
