                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12887615" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2010 01:23:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just kept this simple and used existing API calls to grab the zkWrapper, get all RS nodes, and call size().  It would be nice if ZK provided a getChildrenCount(), so it didn&apos;t have to list all the paths, but I assumed this shouldn&apos;t be a significant performance concern, even for larger clusters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that I also used this opportunity to clean up the class header documentation for HTable &amp;amp; HBaseAdmin.  Feel free to ignore those changes if you have your own doc update.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12887655" author="nspiegelberg" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2010 05:15:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Found the API I needed.   zk.exists() returns a Stat class, which contains the children count.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12887942" author="stack" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2010 19:22:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. Thank you for the patch Nicolas. Applied TRUNK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12927966" author="streamy" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 19:38:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is in some 0.89 branches but was left out from 0.90 (I guess during master rewrite commit).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12927968" author="streamy" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 19:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like the documentation changes made it, just not the HTable.getCurrentNrHRS().  Patch changes implementation of that method (same principle as original patch but slightly different0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12928007" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 21:22:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed your patch Jon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12928012" author="nspiegelberg" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 21:28:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;can we add some explicit comment in there about purposefully not going to Master for the RS count.  I wouldn&apos;t want a 3rd occurrence of this...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12928051" author="stack" created="Wed, 3 Nov 2010 22:48:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;done&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017420" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:43:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
